  \par
  (In the plane YOX let S be a connected area bounded
  by a closed contour, simple or complex; one supposes that at each point of S
  or its perimeter there is a circle, of non-zero radius, having this point as
  its centre; it is then always possible to subdivide S into regions,
  finite in number and
  sufficiently small for each one of them to be entirely inside a circle
  corresponding to a suitably chosen point in S or on its perimeter)\cite{Raman2015}
